+8.47 KVM_CAP_ASYNC_PF_USERFAULT_EVENTFD
+----------------------------------------
+
+:Architectures: x86
+
+The presence of this capability indicates that the kernel supports
+exitless notification for userfaultfd-based async page faults via the
+``KVM_SET_APF_EVENTFD`` vcpu ioctl. ``KVM_CAP_ASYNC_PF_USERFAULT`` is
+required before userspace can use exitless async page fault notification.
+
+When exitless notification is configured, KVM writes async page fault
+notifications to a kernel-allocated shared ring page instead of exiting to
+userspace. KVM signals an eventfd only when userspace has armed notification
+via the shared page header. Userspace resolves the fault, writes completion
+entries to the completion ring, and signals the completion eventfd. See the
+documentation for ``KVM_SET_APF_EVENTFD`` (section 4.145) for details.
+
